==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|never|Never}} + {{term|land}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An ideal or imaginary place; a [[dreamworld]]. 

====Usage notes====
This term was most famously used in [[w:J.M. Barrie|J.M. Barrie]]'s Book, '''[[w:Peter Pan|Peter Pan]]''', as the name of the fictional island that the Darling children travel to with the title character.

